      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Method",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Make and chill the pastry",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Rub the cold {{unsalted-butter}} (for the pastry) into the {{plain-flour}}, {{icing-sugar}}, and {{fine-sea-salt}} until the mixture resembles coarse sand. Add the egg yolk and 1 to 2 tablespoons of cold water; mix until the dough just comes together. Flatten into a disc, wrap, and refrigerate for 30 minutes.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Blind bake",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Heat the oven to 190°C fan. Roll the pastry to fit the 20×30 cm tin, press into the base and sides, and trim the excess. Line with baking paper and fill with {{baking-beans}}. Bake for 12 minutes, then remove the beans and paper and bake for a further 5 minutes until the base is dry and just beginning to colour. Reduce the oven to 170°C fan.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Add jam and frangipane",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Spread the {{cherry-jam}} over the warm pastry base. Beat the {{unsalted-butter}} (for the filling) and {{caster-sugar}} until pale. Beat in the {{free-range-eggs}} and {{almond-extract}}. Fold in the {{ground-almonds}}. Spread over the jam in an even layer. Press the halved {{glace-cherries}} into the surface.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Bake, 30 to 35 minutes",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Bake at 170°C fan for 30 to 35 minutes until the frangipane is set, golden, and a skewer inserted in the centre comes out clean. Cool completely in the tin before cutting.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      }
    ]
  },
